# Demo App Patterns

## Overview

The demo app (`apps/demo`) is a Next.js 16 App Router application that showcases the Puck
editor. It is private and not published to npm.

## Import Resolution

`@puckeditor/core` is resolved via TypeScript path mapping, NOT via npm:

```json
"paths": {
  "@/core": ["../../packages/core"],
  "@/core/*": ["../../packages/core/*"],
  "@puckeditor/core": ["../../packages/core"],
  "@/plugin-heading-analyzer": ["../../packages/plugin-heading-analyzer"],
  "@/plugin-heading-analyzer/*": ["../../packages/plugin-heading-analyzer/*"]
}
```

`next.config.js` uses `transpilePackages: ["@puckeditor/core", "lucide-react"]`.
Do NOT add `@puckeditor/core` to `package.json` dependencies -- it is a workspace symlink.

## File Organization

- `app/` -- Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- `config/` -- Puck configuration: component definitions, categories, root config, initial data
  - `config/blocks/` -- individual block components (Hero, Card, Grid, etc.)
  - `config/components/` -- layout components (Header, Footer, Section, Layout)
  - `config/index.tsx` -- main config barrel, exports `conf` (avoids name `config` due to Next.js conflict)
  - `config/types.ts` -- typed config using `Config<UserComponents>`
  - `config/root.tsx` -- root component configuration
  - `config/initial-data.ts` -- default page data
- `lib/` -- utilities (demo data hooks, path resolution)

## Routing Pattern

The demo uses catch-all routes for the editor and rendering:

- `app/[...puckPath]/page.tsx` -- renders published Puck pages
- `app/[...puckPath]/client.tsx` -- client component for the editor at `/edit` paths
- `app/custom-ui/[...puckPath]/` -- custom UI variant of the editor

## Adding Demo Blocks

1. Create `config/blocks/YourBlock/index.tsx` with the `ComponentConfig`
2. Add a `styles.module.css` with SUIT CSS class names
3. Import and add to `config/index.tsx` components map and categories
4. The block immediately appears in the editor sidebar

## React Version

The demo uses React 19 (`react@^19.2.1`). Components can use React 19 features.
